# Calculation Engine

## Entry point
`runCalculationEngine(model: TestingModel, project: ProjectSpec): ScheduleOutput`
Pure function — no mutations, no localStorage, no React.

## Extension pattern for a new test type
1. Add the enum value to `TestType` in src/types/index.ts
2. Add it to `ALWAYS_ACTIVE_TEST_TYPES` or `CONDITIONAL_TEST_TYPES`
3. Add a description to `TEST_TYPE_DESCRIPTIONS`
4. Add default estimates to `DEFAULT_SCENARIO_ESTIMATES` in modelHelpers.ts
5. Add test cases to `BASE_TEST_CASES` in testCases.ts
6. If conditional: add its activation logic to `deriveActiveTestTypes()` in projectHelpers.ts
7. Add calibration UI to Step3Scenarios (it auto-renders from the enum — verify it appears)
8. Add a unit test for the activation condition in projectHelpers.test.ts

## Arithmetic helpers (use these, don't inline)
addEstimates(a, b) | scaleEstimate(e, factor) | sumEstimates(array)
All round to nearest 0.25 hrs internally.

## Browser scaling
Only CrossBrowser and ResponsiveMobile use BROWSER_TIER_SCALING.
All other test types ignore the browser tier in cell computation.

## Extending the summary section
Add new line items to `deliverableLineItems` in the ScheduleOutput.
They appear automatically in ScheduleSummary. Update the grand total accumulation loop.
